  "prompt": "Has anyone ever died and then revived? What did they see when they die?",
  "response": "There are numerous accounts of individuals experiencing near-death experiences (NDEs) after clinical death or during life-threatening situations. Reports of NDEs often include phenomena such as a sense of detachment from the body, feelings of peace, the experience of moving through a tunnel, encountering bright lights, and meeting deceased loved ones or spiritual beings. Some people report having a life review, where they relive significant moments from their lives.\n\nWhile many of these experiences are subjective and vary widely from person to person, they have been the subject of research and discussion within both medical and philosophical domains. Some researchers suggest that NDEs may be influenced by physiological and psychological factors, such as brain activity during hypoxia (lack of oxygen) or the effects of trauma.\n\nIt's important to note that while there are many anecdotal reports of such experiences, scientific understanding of NDEs is still developing, and no definitive conclusions can be drawn about the nature of consciousness or what happens after death.",
